<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UAE Citizens Urged to Keep Away From Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates has
called on its citizens to keep away from drugs, reported official
WAM news agency on Sunday, one day before the World Anti-Drugs Day.
</P>
<P>
"As an Arab and Islamic society, we should reject this trend
which is increasingly taking toll all over the world. Islam orders
us to distance ourselves from anything that leads to death,"
Interior Minister Mohammed Saeed Al Badi said.
</P>
<P>
After releasing a statement to mark the World Anti-Drugs Day,
Badi advised the Emirates' parents to instill patriotic values in
their children and to protect them from all forms of delinquency.
</P>
<P>
Badi also warned that "gangs of drug-pushers" were still
awaiting chances to bring in these poisons to destroy the rich-oil
country.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, UAE has so far been successful in
containing the drug menace, which has become an international
concern to both individuals and governments.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the authorities have worked out plans to

monitor drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
"We have also been able to provide proper treatment for the
addicts in order to re-integrate them in society as good citizens,"
Badi added, without giving details about the drug addicts in his
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
