<HEADLINE> Urgent: Japan's Ruling Coalition Wins Absolute Majority in Lower House Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Japan's three-party ruling coalition
won an absolute majority in Sunday's general election for the
House of Representatives by securing a combined 271 seats in the
480-seat lower house, final returns of the polls showed.
</P>
<P>
The figure is much higher than the 254-seat target set by the
ruling bloc, which comprises the Liberal Democratic Party (LDP),
the New Komeito party and the New Conservative Party (NCP).
</P>
<P>
Such a result will allow the governing coalition to pass bills
at all lower house standing committees even without the chairman's
vote.
</P>
<P>
The LDP garnered 233 seats, while the New Komeito and the NCP
gained 31 seats and seven seats respectively. 
</P>
