<HEADLINE> Britain's PM to Discuss Europe With German Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
will later this week fly to Germany to discuss with German
Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder the future of the European Union, a
government spokesman said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"There is obviously a discussion about the future of Europe,and
we feel comfortable in that debate," a spokesman in the Downing
Street said.
</P>
<P>
But he denied Blair's government felt it was losing control
over the debate about Europe or that London felt out of step with
Paris and Berlin, both appear to be promoting greater European
integration.
</P>
<P>
"In terms of the debate on Europe, we believe we are in a very
strong position in Europe because of the way we are engaging," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Blair is scheduled to visit Berlin and dine with Schroeder on
Thursday.The meeting will take place the day after a major Franco-
German summit.
</P>
<P>
France's President Jacques Chirac arrived in Berlin on Monday
for two-day visit in Germany. Chirac said over the weekend that he
believed the European Union could have its own constitution within
two years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
