<HEADLINE> Greek Gov't Urged to Take Measures to Fight Drug Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The left-wing political parties in
Greece Monday urged the Greek government to take immediate
measures to combat the growing narcotics problem in the country.
</P>
<P>
In messages marking Monday's International Anti-Drug Day, the
Communist Party of Greece (KKE) said that it was struggling to
create a wider social movement that would fight the causes of the
problem, and founded its policy on prevention and cure, as well as
rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
The Coalition of the Left and Progress (SYN) Monday also
called for drastic reinforcement of the detoxification communities
and the speedy establishment of more such programs.
</P>
<P>
To show their opposition to the use of drugs, about 400
teenagers of a rehabilitation center and their parents marched
through Athens Monday while a concert was hosted by Greece's
Health Ministry, with cooperation of a drug rehabilitation center.
</P>
<P>
In the southern Greek island of Crete, police Monday uprooted
650 cannabis trees in the region of Krasi near the town of Malia.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, drug-related deaths are on the rise in Greece
which ranks second in drug-related deaths among the European Union
's 15 member-states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
