<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The southern Africa would not
be able to develop its economy if its debt burden is not lifted,
South African Deputy President Jacob Zuma said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Because of the crippling debt burden, the living standard of
the people in southern Africa can not be improved, Zuma said at an
ongoing special session of the United Nations General Assembly on
social development in Geneva.
