<HEADLINE> Iran's Elite Force Reinforced with Homemade Helicopters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Two Iranian-made attack helicopters
have been delivered to the air force of the country's elite Islamic
Revolution Guards Corps (IRGC), the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Shabaviz 2061 helicopters were designed and manufactured by
the Organization of Aviation Industries (OAI) affiliated to the
Defense Ministry and the logistics of the armed forces, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
