manufacturing copters in the past three years, said Mohammad Hassan
Tulaei, managing director of the organization. But he did not
disclose the major features of the new, homemade attack copter.
</P>
<P>
He said the organization supplies attack, cargo, training
aircraft as well as gliders to the air forces of the army and the
IRGC.
</P>
<P>
The official also disclosed that test flight of the first
Iranian-made passenger plane, "Iran-140," will be carried out soon.
</P>
<P>
The Iran-140 passenger plane has the capacity to carry 52
passengers, he said, adding that the organization is also giving
maintenance services to the airplanes of the armed forces. 
</P>
