<HEADLINE> Arabs Condemn Visit by Algerian Journalists to Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- An Arab organization of journalists
on Monday condemned a visit paid by a group of Algerian journalists
to Israel, the first of its kind, and said that they should be
punished.
</P>
<P>
The Cairo-based Federation of Arab Journalists (FAJ) denounced
the visit as a violation of its resolutions which opposes
normalization steps with Israel before a just and comprehensive
peace is realized in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The journalists who have not adhered to the boycott should be
punished, said a statement released by the federation, which groups
the journalists' unions of all Arab countries. But it did not
specify the punishment.
</P>
<P>
The statement expressed the federation's belief that most of the
Algerian people are opposed to normalization with Israel at the
current stage when it still occupies Arab territories.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian journalists and a number of academics began the
groundbreaking visit to Israel Monday with a meeting with Foreign
Minister David Levy. The Algerians have been invited by the Israeli
Foreign Ministry. The Algerian government was reportedly aware of
the trip. 
