<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Anti-Trust Body Raids Dutch KPN Telecom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The European Union's anti-trust
authorities on Monday raided the KPN Telecom NV to investigate
whether the leading Dutch telecoms company was involved in a
possible price cartel.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, the executive body of the 15-nation
bloc, has the authority to investigate companies that it suspects
of hampering fair competition within the union.
</P>
<P>
Some civil servants from the commission's competition
department last week made photocopies of the books of the KPN
Telecom, according to the Hague-based company.
</P>
<P>
"Apparently there has been a complaint about the price
agreements between us and other telecoms companies," said a KPN
Telecom spokesperson on Monday. 
</P>
