<HEADLINE> Li Peng on International Situation, China's Domestic Policies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, June 26 (Xinhua) -- It's the views of the Chinese people
that the people of a country will decide what system the country
will set up and what path the country will take, Li Peng, Chairman
of the Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress (
NPC), said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with President of the Ukrainian TV "New Channel,
" Aleksander Tkachenko, the top Chinese legislator elaborated on
the international situation and China's domestic polices.
</P>
<P>
The situation of the world is a focus of discussion of the
international community at present, he said.
</P>
<P>
In reply to a question raised by Tkachenko that there is a
prediction that China and the United States will become the two
polars of the world in the future, Li said he doesn't agree with
this point of view, as such a prediction goes against the reality
as well as the trends of development of the world.
</P>
<P>
China has always welcomed multipolarity and does not favor a
bipolar world or a unipolar world, since multipolarity is
beneficial to world peace and development, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Li pointed out that China is still a developing country with a
population of 1.25 billion and a weak economic foundation and will
have to make long-term persisting efforts to build the country
into a moderately developed country in the mid-21st century.
</P>
<P>
Politically, China is opposed to hegemonism and is not after
hegemonism, and will never practice hegemonism even after it
becomes powerful, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li said that some people deliberately exaggerate the strength
of China and spread the allegation of so-called "China threat."
Actually, these people do not wish China to become powerful, and
their assertion that China will become one of the world's two
polars is similar to the formulation of "China threat."
</P>
<P>
On China's domestic policies, Li said China's policies of
making economic development its central task, adopting reform and
open-up, practicing socialist market economy and ruling the
country by law are all summation of the people's practical
experience and embody the fundamental interests of the people.
</P>
<P>
He added that China has found the road of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics and practice has proved that China
has embarked on the right path.
</P>
<P>
Li arrived here Sunday for a three-day official goodwill visit
to Ukraine, the last leg of his six-nation tour. He has already
visited Yugoslavia, Slovenia, Croatia, Slovakia and Azerbaijan.
</P>
</TEXT>
