<HEADLINE> Slovak President in Critical Health Condition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The health condition of Slovak
President Rudolf Schuster has worsened with both pneumonia and
problems with blood coagulability, according to reports from the
Czech news agency.
</P>
<P>
The state has not changed since this morning, said Josef
Leikert, a presidential spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters that Schuster is still connected to the
respirator and under intensive treatment with antibiotics.
However, he added that the intestines, where a hole was discovered,
had started to function properly again.
</P>
<P>
Schuster was hospitalized on June 14 with a high fever.
Doctors examined the president and found a puncture in his colon.
Then Schuster underwent two "life-saving" emergency operations,
the first for his gut and the second for a massive abdominal
infection.
</P>
<P>
Schuster's condition temporarily improved on Sunday but then
deteriorated again. Doctors performed tracheotomy on him to
relieve the difficulty in breathing. They indicated that
Schuster's life was in danger.
</P>
<P>
Three Czech specialists from the team looking after President
Vaclav Havel and Havel's personal doctor Ilja Kotik are reportedly
to be in Bratislava to help Slovak colleagues.
</P>
<P>
Schuster, 66, was elected president last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
