<HEADLINE> Venus Williams, Hingis Win in First Round at Wimbledon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- World number one Martina Hingis of
Switzerland and fifth-seeded American Venus Williams won in women'
s singles first round at the Wimbledon tennis championships here
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Both won in straight sets, with Hingis pulling off a 6-1, 6-2
victory over Spaniard Angeles Montolio while Williams beating
Kveta Hrdlickova of the Czech Republic 6-3, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
By winning the match, Hingis avoided a repeat of her 1999
Wimbledon humilation where he was defeated in the first round by
Australian qualifier Jelena Dokic.
</P>
<P>
Montolio was apparently no match for Hingis, except in the
final game where she saved seven match points.
</P>
<P>
Hingis no faces China's Yi Jing-Qian, a 6-2, 6-1 winner over
Italian qualifier Giulia Casoni.
</P>
<P>
Williams started her match sluggishly, losing her serve twice
in the first set including her opening service game.
</P>
<P>
But the American kept up the pressure with powerful forehands
which Hrdlickova failed to return time and again.
</P>
<P>
Williams wrapped up the second set in 21 minutes after
Hrdlickova double-faulted on match point. 
</P>
</TEXT>
