<HEADLINE> Shanghai Sees Highest Temperature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai residents met with their
hottest day of this summer today, with the highest temperature
reaching 35 degrees Celsius -- a rarity during the rainy period in
the southern Yangtze River region.
</P>
<P>
Blue skies and bright sunshine brightened local people's
outlook after nearly two weeks of drizzling rain.
</P>
<P>
University students flocked to air-conditioned libraries on
campuses to prepare for the college entrance exams on July 7-9.
Comfortably-chilled department stores and buses were filled with
people dodging the heat, and sunglasses, sun shades, icy drinks
and fruit sold extremely well throughout the city today.
</P>
<P>
Cafes, tea houses and bars, which normally have few daytime
customers, had tables filled with thirsty customers all day long.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecasters predict the 35-degree temperature will
continue through Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
