<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Digital China Forum Held in Central Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The two-day Digital China Forum
began today in Wuhan, capital of central China's Hubei Province,
as a part of the series of forums already held in Hong Kong,
Beijing and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Organizers said the meeting will focus on Internet technology
and development, Internet opportunities, and e-commerce. Training
centers on e-commerce will be available to forum-goers seeking a
basic understanding of on-line business, and how enterprises use
e-trade.
</P>
<P>
The forum aims to accelerate the use of Internet in work units,
governments, and also families in China. Famed entrepreneurs in e-
commerce from the United States, Singapore, and the Chinese
mainland, Hong Kong and Taiwan will share ideas with participants
during the forum.
</P>
<P>
Similar meetings will be held soon in Chengdu and Guangzhou.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
