<DOCNO> XIE20000626.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Scenic City Plans to Control Auto Emission by Rule </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A rule aimed at controlling auto
exhaust emission and improving air pollution in Hangzhou, capital
of east China's Zhejiang Province, was submitted for approval
today to the Standing Committee of the Provincial People's
Congress.
</P>
<P>
The rule, if it passes, will ban the registration, sales,
production and operation of cars not up to the required emission
standard.
</P>
<P>
According to the local transportation department, the city's
number of cars is increasing at annual rate of 20 percent.
Hangzhou now has 300,000 motor vehicles.
</P>
<P>
With a population of 1.7 million, Hangzhou is a scenic city
well-known for its West Lake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
