<HEADLINE> Outer Ring Road Opens in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A 60-km outer ring expressway as
well as a number of bridges, overpasses and roads opened to
traffic today in Guangzhou, a prominent city in south China.
</P>
<P>
The transportation upgrade is part of the city's efforts to
improve its infrastructure, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
The speed limit for the new expressway ranges from 80 to 100 km
per hour, a local official source said, adding that the road
should help to ease Guangzhou's traffic jam problem. 
