<HEADLINE> Xinhua Photo List for June 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Following is the photo list for
June 26 released by Xinhua:

1. Chinese President Jiang Zemin meets with visiting Spanish Prime
Minister Jose Maria Aznar in Beijing.

2. Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan delivers a speech at the seminar
on UN peacekeeping operations in Beijing. British Secretary of
State for Defense Geoff Hoon also attended the seminar.

3. Chinese President Jiang Zemin meets a Taiwanese trade
delegation in Beijing.

4. Chen Xinyuan from Taiwan and five other drug traffickers are
escorted by the police after being sentenced to death in Fuzhou,
capital of east China's Fujian province.

5. The water level of the Harbin section of the Songhuajiang River
reaches its lowest point due to the heavy drought in the area in
northeast China.

6. Some posters expressing the enthusiasm of the Chinese for the
bidding of the 2008 Olympics can be seen in streets and metro
stations of Beijing.

7. 10 legislators, journalists and family members of the prisoners
are appointed as the outside-prison supervisors by the Beijing
Prison Administration to increase its transparency in law
enforcement in Beijing.

8. A Tibetan teacher gives a lesson at a primary school beside the
Tuotuo River, source of the Yangtze River.

9. Police destroy confiscated drugs in Quanzhou, coastal city of
eastern Fujian province.

10. Some tourists enjoy sand sliding in Shapotou, new tourism site
in northwestern Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.  
</P>
