<HEADLINE> Indonesia Imposes Emergency State in Maluku, North Maluku </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Earlier Monday, Chief of the Indonesian National Police Gen.
Rusdihardjo said that the state of civil emergency have been in
force since Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"The civilian emergency status has been in force since Sunday
and we hope that it will be effective in overcoming the situation
there.This move will be more effective to overcome situation there,
"Rusdihardjo said.
</P>
<P>
Maluku province and the neighboring province of North Maluku
has witnessed communal bloodshed involving Muslims and Christians
for nearly two years. More than two thousands people have been
killed during the bloodshed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
