<HEADLINE> Outstanding CPC Members And Party Organizations Cited in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A meeting was held today in the
Chinese capital to cite the outstanding Communist Party of China (
CPC) members and Party organizations in government institutions on
the eve of the 79th anniversary of the founding of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, Chinese Vice President and Standing Committee member
of the Political Bureau of CPC Central Committee, and Vice Premier
Li Lanqing, also a Standing Committee member of the Political
Bureau, attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Hu congratulated the honored party units and members on behalf
of the Central Committee of the CPC and the State Council, China's
highest governing body.
</P>
<P>
He praised the roles play by party members and organizations at
government institutions in ensuring the smooth operation of the
State Council's institutional reform, as well as the achievements
scored in studying Chinese President Jiang Zemin's instruction on
the Party's role.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's instruction says that the Communist Party represents
the development requirements of China's advanced social productive
forces, the progressive course of China's advanced culture, and
the fundamental interests of the overwhelming majority of the
Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Hu urged Party organizations at the government institutions to
focus attention on party building and serve the people
wholeheartedly.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, 223 outstanding Party members and units were
awarded medals and certificates.
</P>
<P>
In another development, Wei Jianxing, Standing Committee member
of the Political Bureau and president of the All-China Federation
of Trade Unions (ACFTU), today also urged trade unions members at
all levels to study Jiang's instructions.
</P>
<P>
Wei made the call at a meeting of the presidium of the ACFTU
which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Jiang's instruction is very important for
strengthening party building under the new historical conditions,
adding that the trade unions should grasp the opportunity to make
breakthrough in establishing trade unions in new enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
