<HEADLINE> Beijing Raises Social Security Benefits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Beijing City will slightly raise
its minimum wage and social security benefits from July 1 this
year, said Sun Yan, deputy director of the Municipal Labor and
Social Security Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Sun said today that the lowest monthly wage in the Chinese
capital will be adjusted from 400 yuan to 412 yuan (about 8.3 yuan
equals to one US dollar).
</P>
<P>
The standards for the unemployment benefits, retirement
pensions and the basic living assurance for laid-off workers will
also go up marginally, by 7 to 11 yuan.
</P>
<P>
This is the fifth time Beijing has raised its minimum wage and
social security benefits, the official said.
</P>
<P>
According to an official figure, Beijing now has 78,000 laid-
off workers, about 55,000 of whom need to draw basic living
assistance from the government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
