<HEADLINE> Nigeria, Morocco Sign Pact to Boost Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria and Morocco have signed a
pact to strengthen bilateral ties and forge a common economic
front for the benefit of their people.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian press Monday quoted Nigerian government officials
as saying on Sunday that the agreement was signed during the
inaugural session of the Nigerian-Morocco Joint Commission
attended by Nigeria's Minister of State for Foreign Affairs, Dubem
Onyia and his Moroccan counterpart, Taib Fassi Fishri.
</P>
<P>
