<HEADLINE> COMESA Expresses Confidence on Free Trade Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Common Market for Eastern and
Southern Africa (COMESA) has expressed confidence in establishing
Free Trade Area (FTA) by October 31, 2000.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony of the COMESA communication workshop in
Lusaka on Monday, Assistant Secretary-General Sindiso Ngwenya
said that COMESA will form the largest and the first FTA in
Africa.
</P>
<P>
"We have no doubt that the full removal of tariff and
non-tariff barriers in COMESA by October 31, 2000 will succeed in
generating business opportunities for all the citizens of COMESA,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
In the same breadth, he said: "We should all be cognizant of
the fast changing pace in the globalization of world trade not
only in goods but also in services which include
telecommunications."
</P>
<P>
As the rules will continue to be made under the auspices of the
World Trade Organization (WTO), it is beneficial that the COMESA
member states combine their efforts in the negotiations process,
he added.
</P>
<P>
COMESA does offer the opportunity to create a truly successful
regional block that will attract foreign direct investment and
harness the potential of COMESA economies by offering a large
market and fair competition between companies operating in the
region, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
