<HEADLINE> Warning Announced Possible Volcanic Eruption in Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Meteorological Agency
announced Monday a warning that a volcanic eruption could possibly
happen on Miyakejima Island, south of central Japan's Izu
Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The Meteorological Agency issued the alert around 7:30 p.m.
local time after seismic activity on the island became strong at
about 6:30 p.m., with successive mild earthquakes taking place.
</P>
<P>
Warnings are usually issued when volcanic activities become
especially intense and urgent counter-measures are required.
</P>
<P>
Miyakejima, which has a population of about 3,800, is part of
the Izu Islands, administered by the Tokyo metropolitan government.
</P>
<P>
The highest peak on the island, the 814-meter Mt. Oyama, had
its latest eruption in October 1983, which has destroyed 413 out
of some 500 buildings, including residential houses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
