<HEADLINE> Beijing Launches Drug-Control Publicity Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Beijing today held a series of
activities to publicize the city's drug control campaign as part
of International Anti-Drug Day.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting this morning, 100 individuals and 50 units were
commended by the Beijing Drug-Control Committee for their
contributions to the control of drugs in the past year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, volunteers and drug-control officials in the Chinese
capital set up 111 temporary drug education centers to give basic
information about drug prevention and control.
</P>
<P>
More than 500,000 anti-drug brochures were distributed in
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Beijing set up a permanent drug-control education base last
year, which has reportedly received more than 500,000 visitors
since its opening.
</P>
<P>
According to Qiang Wei, head of the Beijing Drug-Control
Committee, the city has investigated more than 2,000 drug-related
criminal cases since 1992, confiscating over 290 kg of drugs in
all.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992 a total of 12,000 people have been registered as
drug users, and more than 7,000 of them have been rehabilitated,
official statistics show. 
</P>
