<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Artificial Rain Eases Drought in NE China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- People in northeast China's
Liaoning Province experienced a delightful rain this weekend after
almost two weeks of sweltering heat.
</P>
<P>
Two cloud-seeding helicopters flew for ten hours Saturday,
spraying silver iodide into a cold air mass moved from the west
into the province. As a result, 14 cities in the area received
moderate to heavy rain, and some regions in the province even had
heavy storms, which lessened the serious drought in over one
million ha of dried land.
</P>
<P>
However, the local meteorological bureau warned that the
artificial rain will not solve the drought problem, as the water
supply in most reservoirs has not reached the necessary level.
</P>
<P>
Another cloud-seeding attempt is expected at the end of this
month as another cold air mass is to pass through the province.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000626.0138 </DOCNO>
