<HEADLINE> East China Builds Dual-Frequency Mobile Telecom Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Mobile Telecom in east
China signed a contract today with four other telecom companies to
build a dual-frequency mobile telecom network.
</P>
<P>
The project is to improve voice transmission quality, to
develop mobile Internet technology, and to support WAP (wireless
application protocol) mobile phones and short message sending.
</P>
<P>
The financing of 1.1 billion yuan (about 132 million U.S.
dollars) came from five parties, including mobile phone developers
Nokia and Siemens.
</P>
<P>
When finished at the end of this year, the capacity of the new
network will total 10 million exchange lines and seven million
mobile phone lines.
</P>
<P>
There are now four million mobile phone users in the eastern
province. 
</P>
