<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Meets Iranian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) Tung Chee Hwa Monday hosted a
luncheon in honor of visiting President of the Islamic Republic of
Iran, Seyyed Mohammad Khatami, at Government House.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting held prior to the luncheon, Tung updated the
Iranian President on the progress of Hong Kong's economic recovery
since the Asian financial crisis and briefed him on the successful
implementation of "One Country, Two Systems" in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The government aimed to develop Hong Kong into a hub for
innovation and technology in the region, he added.
</P>
<P>
Khatami is in Hong Kong following a trip to the Chinese
mainland.
</P>
<P>
Other government officials attending the meeting included Chief
Secretary for Administration, Anson Chan; Financial Secretary
Donald Tsang; and Secretary for Trade and Industry, Chau Tak Hay.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
