<DOCNO> XIE20000626.0142 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Wipes Out Locusts (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to latest official statistics, plagues of oriental
grasshoppers destroyed 1.69 million hectares of crops in China by
June 22, including 215,300 hectares in Xinjiang.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a total of 3.88 million hectares of farmland have
been swarmed by Italian locusts.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural experts blamed the disaster for dry weather and
locusts from neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
"The locust plague will get worse in the coming years in China,
" said Zhu Enlin, an expert from the Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
"The worst-hit areas will be the Yellow River valley, the Bohai
Sea area and the western part of south China's island province of
Hainan," he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that about 30 million yuan (3.61 million US dollars)
has been allocated to deal with the locusts. However, another 30
million yuan (3.61 million US dollars) is needed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
