<DOCNO> XIE20000626.0143 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Wipes Out Locusts (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- China is taking effective measures
to control plagues of locusts, according to sources from the
Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
A total of 466,700 hectares of farmland hit by oriental
grasshoppers have already been brought under control in the
provinces of Hebei, Shandong, Henan, Anhui, Shanxi, Shaanxi and
Jiangsu and Tianjin Municipality, accounting for 65 percent of the
locust-stricken land.
</P>
<P>
Ministry sources said that about two thirds of the locusts have
been eradicated in the worst-hit areas in Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
China has used ten aircraft and 90,000 pieces of machinery to
spray more than 11 million tons of chemical and biological
insecticides. Nearly 280,000 workers have been called in to rid
the locusts.
</P>
<P>
This summer's locust plague covers the middle and lower reaches
of the Yellow River, Xinjiang, the Bohai Sea area in north China,
as well as some areas in southwest and northeast China.
</P>
<P>
There are 1,000 to 5,000 locusts per square meter in some of
the worst-hit areas, far above the state-set standard for
prevention and eradication.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
