<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seminar on UN Peacekeeping Operations Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and the United Kingdom (
UK) Secretary of State for Defense Geoff Hoon attended the opening
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Tang said at the ceremony that the UN's role in international
affairs is irreplaceable in the new century.
</P>
<P>
Tang said UN peacekeeping operations should continue to follow
the gist and principles of the UN Charter and a series of other
basic principles already proved to be effective, including getting
consent first from the country concerned, observing neutrality,
and using military forces for self-defense only.
</P>
<P>
Tang said as permanent members of the UN Security Council,
China and the UK shoulder important responsibilities in
safeguarding world peace and security, adding that the present
seminar will further promote and develop bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Hoon agreed that the UK and China bear special responsibilities
for maintaining global peace and security. Both countries share
similar views on many important world issues.
</P>
<P>
The convening of the seminar demonstrated the further
intensifying of cooperation between the two countries and will
undoubtedly push forward relations and bilateral cooperation, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The two-day seminar is organized by foreign ministries of China
and the UK. More than 50 officials and experts attended the
seminar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
