<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UEFA Rules Kluivert Scores Three Goals Instead of Four </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Patrick Kluivert's third goal for
the Netherlands against Yugoslavia in Sunday's European soccer
championship quarter-final has been ruled by UEFA as an own goal.
</P>
<P>
It means that Kluivert scored a hat-trick instead of a record-
breaking four goals as the Dutchmen won 6-1.
</P>
<P>
UEFA said on Monday it decided a Yugoslav player had put the
ball into his own net on the third goal originally credited to
Kluivert.
</P>
<P>
Kluivert had been the first player to score four goals in a
match at a European championships finals but the record books will
now be amended to show he scored three. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
