<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Customs Fights Drug Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has intensified its
crackdown on drug trafficking this year.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months, Shanghai customs seized 330 grams of
methamphetamine, known as "ice," in 10 air mail bags, latest
statistics indicated.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai customs also uncovered 15 smuggling cases, involving
heroin and ice amounting to 1,440 grams.
</P>
<P>
Eight suspects involved were detained, and six of whom have
been arrested. Among them, three persons had been sentenced, with
the heaviest penalty of up to 15 years.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai customs officers said in recent years smugglers tended
to smuggle methamphetamine through mail bags which were more
difficult to discover.
</P>
<P>
To deal with this situation, customs officers have adopted
state-of-the-art equipment to check mail.
</P>
<P>
In April this year, two drug traffickers attempted to hide
drugs in medicine capsules and mail them abroad. All suspects
involved in the case were detained by Shanghai customs officers
within 48 hours.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai customs have also tightened monitoring passengers. In
March, a suspect identified as Xu was stopped at Hongqiao Airport
for bringing in drugs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
