<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Builds Cross-sea Bridge to Develop Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- China has completed the structure
of a cross-sea bridge in the port city of Ningbo in eastern
Zhejiang Province in a move to develop an island in East China Sea.
</P>
<P>
The 4,500-meter-long bridge involves a total investment of 200
million yuan (about 24 million U.S. dollars) from the China
International Trust and Investment Corporation (CITIC).
</P>
<P>
The bridge links the mainland and Daxie Island, close to the
port of Beilun.
</P>
<P>
The structure of the bridge was finally completed on June 24.
</P>
<P>
CITIC plans to develop Daxie Island to turn it into an economic
development zone with port, industrial production base and free
trade zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
