<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing To Elect New Neighborhood Committees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A number of new neighborhood
committee members and leaders will soon be elected in Beijing's 18
districts and counties, according to Chu Guoqing, an official in
charge of neighborhood committee elections in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Chu told a press conference today that neighborhood committee
elections in the capital are expected to be over by the end of
July.
</P>
<P>
"Neighborhood committee elections are an important part of
China's grass-roots democratic construction. It will also play an
important role in improving city management and services," Chu
said.
</P>
<P>
These elections are held every three years according to law.
More than 4,000 neighborhood committees in Beijing will be re-
elected this time.
</P>
<P>
"Like in the past, elections will be open and fair. Voting will
be through a secret ballot", the official said.
</P>
<P>
"Voters can also decide whether they want direct elections or
indirect elections", he said.
</P>
<P>
The neighborhood committee is a self-governed, non-governmental
organization in urban China. There are 4,610 neighborhood
committees in Beijing and 117,000 nationwide.  
</P>
</TEXT>
