<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian President Calls for Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Iranian President
Seyyed Mohammad Khatami stressed on Iran's policy of developing
economy in a keynote speech delivered at a seminar on Iran's trade
opportunities held here Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Reforming our monetary system, reorganizing the financial
market, protecting and encouraging foreign investment by
guaranteeing the security of the invested capital, revising our
economic regulation and tax system are now among the overall
economic policies of Iran," said the president, who is on the last
leg of his five-day state visit to China beginning in Beijing on
June 22.
</P>
<P>
This is the president's first trip to China since he took
office in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The president emphasized on Iran's special position in the Mid-
East as a bridge between Europe and Asia and a link between two
rich gas fields and oil pools in the world -- the Persian Gulf and
the Caspian Sea, as well as the rich oil and gas reserves of Iran
itself and Iran's human resources.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, as
one of the main economic and commercial centers in Southeast Asia,
with great capability in the fields of production, business
management, banking, marketing and commerce, will further economic
cooperation with Iran.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Khatami appealed for elimination of tension and
enhancement of mutual understanding between cultures and
civilizations.
</P>
<P>
"Mutual understanding and respect will foster greater
cooperation and repel any form of contention and conflict," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is aimed to explore ways in which Hong Kong and
Iran can develop business together, said an official of the Hong
Kong Trade Development Council, the organizer of the seminar.
</P>
<P>
Iran, with a population of over 65 million, represents a new
market of great potential in the Mid-East region, said the
official.  
</P>
</TEXT>
