<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets Mauritanian Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee, met here today with Mohamed
Yehdhih Ould Moctar El Hacen, visiting general secretary of the
Mauritanian Democratic and Social Republic Party (PRDS).
</P>
<P>
Wei, who is also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, said that China and Mauritania have supported each
other since the establishment of bilateral ties in 1965, and have
carried out exchanges in numerous fields.
</P>
<P>
China is grateful for Mauritania's adherence to the one-China
policy and its support on human rights, Wei said, adding that
China hopes to work together with Mauritania to realize overall
development of bilateral relations in the new century.
</P>
<P>
Wei also noted that the friendly ties between the CPC and the
PRDS have helped increase mutual understanding and friendship
between the two peoples and two countries.
</P>
<P>
The CPC treasures its cooperation with the PRDS, and hopes to
promote party-to-party relations and state-to-state ties in the
new century, he added.
</P>
<P>
Hacen said that Mauritania believes that the CPC and the
Chinese people are fully capable of dealing with all kinds of
problems and make greater achievements in the cause of national
construction.
</P>
<P>
He also hoped that the friendly ties between Mauritania and
China would be further consolidated through his current visit.
</P>
<P>
The Mauritanian guests are here at the invitation of the CPC.
</P>
</TEXT>
