<HEADLINE> China, Spain Vow to Expand Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Spanish Prime Minister
Jose Maria Aznar said here today that the Spanish government will
spare no efforts to support its enterprises to develop economic
cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister made the remark in a speech today at the
closing ceremony of the Sino-Spanish Entrepreneurs Seminar.
</P>
<P>
Aznar spoke highly of China's achievements in economic
construction. He said that he believes China will play an even
bigger role in international economic affairs after its entry to
the World Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo briefed the participants on
China's economic situation.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that the Chinese government attaches great importance
to developing long-term, stable and friendly relations with Spain.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the two countries have made achievements in
bilateral cooperation in various fields, said Wu, adding that
there is still great potential in bilateral economic and trade
cooperation between the two countries on the basis of equality and
mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Wu urged entrepreneurs from the two countries to explore new
ways and areas for economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that China welcomes more investment from Spain and
Spain's participation in developing China's western regions.
</P>
