<BODY>
<HEADLINE> MOE Approves Setup of 47 Higher Learning Institutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Education (MOE)
has approved the setup of 47 institutions of higher learning,
including 39 regular colleges and 8 vocational schools, all of
which will enroll students this year, said a MOE official today.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Development and Planning department of MOE
pointed out that such a measure will help to change the current
situation where most institutions of higher learning are located
in provincial capital cities.
</P>
<P>
The 39 colleges, most of which located in comparatively
developed cities, include Tangshan Normal College, Langfang Normal
College, Nanjing Xiaozhuang College, and Huainan Normal College.
</P>
<P>
The 8 vocational schools include the Nanjing Forest Police
Academy, the Shanxi Police Academy, and the Hunan No.1 Normal
School.
</P>
<P>
Experts say such a measure will greatly reform higher education
in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
