<HEADLINE> Share Prices End Lower on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) shed 7.19 points to
close at 2,027.12 points.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 313.82 million units valued at
440.67 million Singapore dollars (254.16 million U.S. dollars).
There were 139 rising issues against 130 declining ones with 276
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was the 33.86 million parcel by Adroit which
was transacted at 0.775 Singapore dollars per share. AddvalTech
was the second most heavily traded stock with 24.76 million shares
done. Medi-Rad was the next with 15.83 million counters changing
hands.
</P>
<P>
DBS led gainers of the day edging up 40 cents to close at 21.70
Singapore dollars. Chartered moved up 20 cents to finish at 15.30
Singapore dollars. Jar Mat inched up 16 cents to end at 4.16 U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
SPH was the biggest loser of the day incurring a loss of 90
cents to close at 26.80 Singapore dollars.SPH 100 sank 70 cents to
finish at 26.90 Singapore dollars. Datacrft ended the day at 8.80
U.S. dollars 50 cents lower.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that concerns over U.S. interest-rate hike
continue to weigh on the market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
They noted banking stocks and their non-core listed assets saw
moderate trading activity following last week call by the
Association of Banks in Singapore for local banks to streamline
their business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
