<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Monday across the board in a
shorter trading session as the exchange resumed trading only in
the afternoon following its computer system failure.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 8.38
points to 803.87, slightly above the 800 support level, which
dipped below the 800-mark several times during the trading Monday.
</P>
<P>
The all-share Emas Index closed 1.99 points lower to 200.54,
the Industrial Index dropped 16.52 points to 1,415.11 and the
Second Board Index shed 1.99 points to 206.36.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 424 to 142 while 135 counters were
unchanged and 287 counters untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover declined to 65.772 million shares valued at
299.622 million ringgit (78.84 million U.S. dollars) from 93.729
million shares valued at 476.564 million ringgit (125.41 million U.
S. dollars) last Friday. 
</P>
