<DOCNO> XIE20000626.0207 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Islamic Chamber of Commerce Seeks Cooperation from Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Islamic Chamber of
Commerce and Industry (ICCI) needs cooperation and assistance from
Islamic countries to further improve its performance, its
secretary-general Aqeel A. Al-Jasem said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Acknowledging that "at present, its performance is still not
satisfactory," he said the chamber needed the cooperation and
assistance from all members as it could not face the challenges
alone.
</P>
<P>
He urged more businessmen to attend the ICCI's annual Private
Sector meetings, the next one to be held in Doha, Qatar, in
October.
</P>
<P>
Among the setbacks that pose a hurdle towards enhancing better
cooperation among members is the geographical diversity of Islamic
countries and the varied level of economic development among
Islamic nations, he told reporters after a meeting with the
Malaysian Malay Chambers of Commerce and Industry here.
</P>
<P>
However, he said the ICCI has high hopes of eventually
realizing the proposed Islamic Common Market and would seek ways
to counter these constraints by focusing on inter-Islamic trade.
</P>
<P>
He said that currently, inter-Islamic trade accounted for 11
percent of the world trade, but if petroleum was taken out, there
is only two percent left of Islamic trade.
</P>
<P>
He hoped inter-Islamic trade would reach 30 percent of the
world trade by next year as the chamber prepared for the
challenges of the new millennium, saying the Islamic countries
have everything including the basic resources and manpower.
</P>
<P>
The ICCI is the only institution within the 56-member
Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC), representing the private
sector.
</P>
<P>
The ICCI aims at strengthening closer collaboration in the
field of trade, commerce, insurance, shipping, banking, promotion
of investment opportunities and joint ventures in the member
countries, and through its Plan of Action, seeks to offer
promotional, advisory, information, training programs, technical
assistance and other services to the private sectors of the member
countries.
</P>
<P>
The ICCI official is here for the 27th Islamic Conference of
Foreign Ministers (ICFM) which is scheduled to open here Tuesday
by Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
