<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Take Over Air Traffic Control From Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia will take over the
country's air traffic control (ATC) from Singapore, Minister of
Industry and Trade Luhut Binsar Pandjaitan said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Come September, the agreement with Singapore (on ATC) will
expire. The (Indonesian) government wants to do it (the control)
by itself gradually," the minister said in a dialogue with the
Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
He said Indonesia's ATC activities will thereafter be centered
in Batam's Hang Nadim airport.
</P>
<P>
"This (takeover) will also refute allegations that Indonesia
does not have the right technology and human resources (for ATC).
Actually, we do have," the minister said.
</P>
<P>
The handling of the air traffic control by itself would give the
side-benefits of enhancing control and monitoring of the air
territorial stability.
</P>
<P>
"In the past, we have not been maximum in monitoring the
movement of foreign military aircraft entering Indonesia's air
territory. Now that we are going to manage the ATC by ourselves,
the matter will be handled differently," Pandjaitan added.
</P>
</TEXT>
