that they acknowledged President Frederick Chiluba as chairman of
the inter-party talks and urged him to call for a meeting to
discuss the agenda set in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The general elections will be held next year and the
inter-party talks, a dialog mechanism between the country's ruling
and opposition parties, have never held a meeting since December
1998 although a number of opposition parties and non-government
organizations have repeatedly called for the resumption of the
talks. 
