<HEADLINE> Overseas Investors Report More Profits in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Overseas-funded enterprises in
east China's Jiangsu Province have reported more than 5.18 billion
yuan (about 624 million U.S. dollars) in profits for the first
five months of the year, a year-on-year surge of 80.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Local experts say this indicates an improving business
environment for overseas investment in the province.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu has approved some 22,500 overseas-funded businesses
over the past two decades. Over 16,000 are operational.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 of the world's top 500 corporations have already
opened subsidiaries in the province. These businesses are engaged
in a wide variety of industries such as information technology,
machinery, chemicals, and pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
According to the provincial statistics bureau, overseas-funded
companies in Jiangsu generated 25.52 billion yuan (about 3.07
billion U.S. dollars) in industrial added value during the January-
May period this year.
</P>
<P>
Encouraged by growing economic returns, about 600 of the
overseas-funded businesses in the province have increased their
investments by 2.13 billion U.S. dollars since last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
