<HEADLINE> Private Retirement Homes Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Some 1,075 private retirement
homes are now accommodating 24,000 Chinese senior citizens,
according to statistics from the China National Committee on Aging.
</P>
<P>
China has more than 100 million people over 60 who make up 10
percent of the country's 1.2 billion population. It is estimated
that the figure will reach 400 million by the middle of 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
"The traditional ways" of taking care of the aged can no longer
satisfy the increasing number, said an official with the committee.
Family's responsibility will be partly taken over by society, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Usually the family will take care of parents after their
retirement. But with the increasing number of migrants in the
country, old people are hardly being taken well care of. Private
retirement homes are one of the ways available to those who have
no families.
</P>
<P>
At present, the State-run welfare homes for senior citizens and
collective-run old-people's homes have accommodated almost one
million aged people.
</P>
<P>
"Communities should help support the old," Premier Zhu Rongji
called in his government's report early this year.
</P>
<P>
A program aiming to improve welfare among the elderly was
launched this year by the Ministry of Civil Affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
