<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed slightly higher here Monday, contributed mostly by Fletcher
Energy gains.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 3 points higher at 2,016 with a small
turnover of 63.5 million NZ dollars (29.8 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, Fletcher Energy led the market in
gains closing 24 cents higher to 646 cents. Other Fletcher stocks
had little changes with Paper and Building edging up 1 cent each
to 240 and 212 cents respectively, while Forests easing 2 cents to
79 cents.
</P>
<P>
Market heavyweight Telecom slipped further 5 cents to 730 cents,
also down was pay television network Sky TV falling 4 to 411 cents.
</P>
<P>
Discount retailer the Warehouse gained 15 cents to 485 cents,
Independent News 10 to 380 cents, and Auckland Airport 5 to 253
cents.
</P>
<P>
Financial concern Tower fell 8 cents to 502 cents, insurance
giant AMP 5 to 2,000 cents, and the biggest brewer Lion Nathan 1
cent to 476 cents.
</P>
<P>
No 2 stock Carter Holt Harvey closed unchanged at 181 cents.
</P>
</TEXT>
