<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 9 Passengers Gunned Down in East India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The assailants sprayed bullets at the vehicle in Leingangpokpi
area Sunday evening, killing nine passengers, according to the
Press Trust of India.
</P>
<P>
Of the nine killed, seven persons, including two women and the
driver, died on the spot. One passenger succumbed to injuries on
way to hospital and another died at the hospital.
</P>
<P>
No individual or group has claimed the responsibility for the
killing and the motive behind the crime was not known, the sources
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
