<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Host World Marketing Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BANGKOK, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Business persons, marketing
managers, and business executives in Thailand will join their
counterparts from around the world in attending the World
Marketing Conference, to be held here between June 29 and 30, the
Thai News Agency (TNA) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The two-day forum is aimed to enhance competitiveness of
business firms in the globalization by brainstorming ideas of all
parties concerned taking part in the conference, Subhat
Tansatitikorn, a leading Thai business executive was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Her Royal Highness Princess Maha Chakri Sirindhorn would preside
over the opening ceremony of the conference, he said.
</P>
<P>
Honorable guest speakers at the two-day conference would include
Thai Deputy Prime Minister and Commerce Minister Supachai
Panitchpakdi, senior executives of leading firms, he disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Supachai, who will take the leadership of the World Trade
Organization (WTO) over the next two years, will talk about the
global trading trend in the globalizations, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Participants would also discuss the so-called on-line marketing,
and the significance of information technology (IT) amid changing
business practices, said Subhat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
