<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Killed in Ambush in Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A former mayor was critically
wounded but his three companions were killed when they were
ambushed Monday morning in Pampanga province in the northern
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
A police report reaching here said Roy David, former Porac
mayor, was ambushed in Angeles City at about 9:20 a.m. shortly
after coming out from a regular program in a local radio station.
</P>
<P>
David was rushed to the Angeles University Foundation Medical
Center after the ambush. Doctors said he was already out of danger.
</P>
<P>
However, his driver and two other companions were killed by the
still unidentified gunmen.
</P>
<P>
Police teams were dispatched to go after the suspects. Motive
for the ambush is still under investigation.
</P>
<P>
David was the second former town executive to be ambushed in
Central Luzon in two weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
