here Monday afternoon with Spanish Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar,
who arrived here Sunday for a five-day official visit to China.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is still going on at press time.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and Aznar held talks on Sunday, and
witnessed the signing of several documents on cooperation between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
This is the first China visit by Aznar, who is accompanied by a
delegation of more than 300 members, including about 200
entrepreneurs. 
