<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Farmers to Get Training on Pest Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- More than 100,000 rice and vegetable
farmers will be given practical and in-depth training on pest
Control and crop management at 4,200 field schools, The
Independent newspaper reported here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Besides, some 105,000 farmers will receive certain amount of
knowledge on pest and crop management by attending the field
schools in different parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The work will be taken up under the Strengthening Plant
Protection Services Project funded by the Danish International
Development Assistance and executed by the Department of
Agriculture Extension.
</P>
<P>
The farmers do not attend lecture classes. Their fields are the
schools and they learn the knowledge through watching,
experimenting and participating.
</P>
<P>
Danish Ambassador Finn Thilsted and his senior colleagues have
visited some field schools in different districts where farmers
told him the practical training they are receiving would greatly
benefit them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
