<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Political Parties Gear for Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan political parties are
gearing up for the 11th general elections as the term of the
present Parliament is due to end on August 25.
</P>
<P>
Almost all the legality of the political parties in the country
are in the electioneering fray and are getting ready to face the
polls, official Daily News said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The coalition partners of the ruling People's Alliance (PA) are
due to meet this week to finalize the allocation of seats for each
party, an official of the PA was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
They have already started organizational operations for the
11th general elections at grass-root level, according to the
official.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman of the main opposition United National Party
Karunasena Kodituwakku said that his party has been ready to face
elections since January this year.
</P>
<P>
The Mahajana Eksath Peramuna leader Dinesh Gunawardena said his
party was preparing for elections at district level and was in the
process of selecting candidates.
</P>
<P>
The Muslim Congress leader and Minister of Port Development
Reconstruction A.H.M. Ashraff said they were looking to contest as
a separate group and would be contesting mainly in the Eastern
province and in some other districts like Colombo, Kandy, Kalutara
and Puttalam at the forthcoming elections.
</P>
<P>
A Janatha Vimukthi Perumuna (JVP) spokesman said they were in
the final stages of selecting their candidates.
</P>
<P>
Elections Commissioner Dayananda Dissanayake said he was
awaiting official confirmation for the holding of the 11th
Parliamentary elections. 
</P>
