<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Education Important to Create Drug-Free Society: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Deputy Prime
Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said Monday the role of preventive
education is important in ensuring that society will be free from
the drug menace.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah, who is also home minister, called for stepping up
more effective drug prevention program, enforcement and
rehabilitation since drug abuse is a major threat to people's
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The preventive education is an important element in the
prevention's strategy, Abdullah said in his message in conjunction
with the International Anti-Drugs Day Monday.
</P>
<P>
Schools and institutions of higher learning must strive to
create a drug-free society, he said.
</P>
<P>
In this respect, parents and families have their respective
roles in the prevention of drug abuse and creation of a drug-free
society, he said, adding it is the parents who would determine how
their children would behave and as such they should make time and
try to understand problems faced by their children or they would
grow up as a problem to society.
</P>
<P>
The home minister also urged the private sector to introduce
drug prevention policy and program at the work place to prevent
their employees from indulging in drugs.
</P>
<P>
According to the records of the National Drug Agency, 78
percent of drug addicts detected in the country are employed
youths and as such there must be greater program tailored for
youths to educate them on drugs and offer them healthy lifestyle
without drugs, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the new treatment and rehabilitation for drug addicts
must be streamlined to ensure greater effectiveness in addition to
family therapy and work therapy at drug rehabilitation centers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
