<HEADLINE> Weekly Review of Health News in China (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
People's Daily, the leading newspaper in China, published a
commentary last Tuesday calling for speedier reforms of the
medical care system in cities and townships.
</P>
<P>
It said that the reform, together with the establishment of a
basic medical insurance system for urban employees, was aimed at
building up an urban medical care system up to the requirements of
the socialist market economy, boosting the healthy development of
the medical and pharmaceutical industry, and enabling the people
to enjoy fair-priced and quality medical services.
</P>
<P>
 Project HOPE Offering Free Treatment to Gaucher Patients
</P>
<P>
A Gaucher patient from north China's Hebei province has
recently been sent to Beijing Children's Hospital to receive free
medical treatment, becoming the 23rd patient suffering from the
Gaucher Disease whose medical treatment are covered by Project
HOPE, a U.S.-based charity institution.
</P>
<P>
Gaucher Disease is the most common lysosomal storage disease
and the most common genetic disorder among Ashkenazi Jews. It
occurs one out of every 100,000 to 400,000 people worldwide.
</P>
<P>
 Sino-French Pharmaceutical Venture Set Up
</P>
<P>
China Huajin Pharmaceutical Co. and Servier Pharmaceutical Corp.
of France have signed an agreement to set up a joint venture in
Tianjin Municipality.
</P>
<P>
The new Servier Tianjin Pharmaceutical Co., Ltd., with an
investment of 130 million yuan, is located in the economic and
technological development zone in Tianjin, a port city near
Beijing. 
</P>
