<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Announces Scheme for PDS Issuance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's Securities
Commission (SC) has announced transitional arrangements for the
issuance of private debt securities (PDS) and the registration of
prospectuses relating to PDS.
</P>
<P>
The SC said in a statement on Monday that the move would enable
issuers and their advisers to adjust to the new fund-raising
regime for PDS that would be in place with the coming into force
of amendments to securities, company and banking laws.
</P>
<P>
These amendments formulated after consultation with various
industry and professional bodies would make the SC the approving
authority for PDS of any corporation and the registering authority
for prospectuses relating to such PDS from July 1.
</P>
<P>
Under the arrangements, the PDS issuers must comply with the
Companies Act 1965 requirements relating to trust deeds and
prospectuses and the relevant stock exchanges' listing
requirements.
</P>
<P>
The Issuers must obtain a letter of approval from the SC to
avail themselves of the relief granted. The SC is committed to
granting approval within 14 working days from the application date.
</P>
<P>
However, the SC said Issuers of PDS which has been approved by
Bank Negara (State Bank) Malaysia on or before June 30 this year
do not have to comply with the new guidelines on the matter
provided that the issue of the PDS takes place within a period of
six months from the date of the central bank's approval. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
