<HEADLINE> Thailand to Buy 10,000 Water Buffaloes from Laos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is to buy some 10,000
pregnant water buffaloes from Laos, as the number of the creature
in the country is almost extinct due to higher demand for its meat,
the Thai News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Agriculture Minister Arkom Engchuan was quoted by the
news agency as saying that he and a group of senior officials from
the Livestock Development Department would leave for talks with
Laos' Agriculture Ministry soon on the purchasing of the pregnant
mammals.
</P>
<P>
The Bank for Agriculture and Agricultural Cooperatives is
seeking a loan of 100 million baht (about 2.5 million U.S. dollars)
to fund a project which enables Thai farmers to buy buffaloes,
Arkom said.
</P>
<P>
The project will help increase supplies of buffalo meat in
domestic market of Thailand, he added. 
</P>
