<HEADLINE> Myanmar Official on Domestic Drug Eradication Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar's poppy cultivation has
reduced by 30 percent as Myanmar began implementing the 15-year
plan (1999-2014) for total eradication of narcotic drugs, said a
high ranking Myanmar anti-drug official Monday.
</P>
<P>
Colonel Tin Hlaing, chairman of the Myanmar Central Committee
for Drug Abuse Control, in his message on the occasion of the
International Day Against Drug Abuse and Illicit Trafficking, said
that monitoring is done, alternative and better plans are
formulated and implemented for the benefit of national races
residing in the border areas.
</P>
<P>
Tin Hlaing, who is also minister of home affairs, thanked the
Myanmar Anti-Narcotic Association, a non-governmental organization
in the country, for its cooperation in the drug eradication
efforts.
</P>
<P>
He also highly appreciated the cooperation and assistance
rendered by the U.N. Drug Control Program, international
organizations and community in helping Myanmar eradicate drugs.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has laid down two strategies for drug eradication: one
is to designate drug eradication as a comprehensive national
program, the other is to develop the border areas for the total
elimination of poppy cultivation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
