<HEADLINE> Brazil, United States Win in Women's Gold Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Katia da Silva on Sunday scored
seven goals as Brazil routed Trinidad and Tobago 11-0 in
Louisville, Kentucky, to remain unbeaten at the inaugural Women's
Gold Cup soccer tournament.
</P>
<P>
Da Silva scored in the eighth, 18th, 24th, 45th, 55th, 66th and
90th minutes. Other Brazil goals came from Rosana in the 17th
minute, Daniela Alves in the 24th, Cidinha in the 39th on a
penalty kick and Monica in the 60th.
</P>
<P>
The United States, the reigning Olympic and World Cup champion,
beat Costa Rica 8-0 in Sunday's other match.
</P>
<P>
Nikki Serlenga opened the scoring in the 10th minute with
Shannon MacMillan following in the 12th and Susan Bush bulging the
half-time edge to 3-0 with a goal in the 27th minute.
</P>
<P>
Christie Welsh added a goal in the 47th minute and Serlenga
added her second and third goals in the 53rd and 63rd minutes.
Welsh added her second goal in the 81st minute and Sara Whalen
fired a turnaround shot in the 83rd. 
</P>
