<HEADLINE> Swoopes Makes US Olympic Basketball Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Sheryl Swoopes, a 1996 Olympic
gold medalist and two-time All-WNBA first-team selection, was
named the final member of the United States women's Olympic
basketball team on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Swoopes won a gold medal as a member of the 1996 squad that
went 60-0 in exhibition and Olympic action, as she averaged 13.0
points per game. She was second on the team with 31 assists during
the Atlanta Olympics.
