<HEADLINE> Chinese Surgeons Remove Huge Liver Tumor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese surgeons recently
successfully removed a malignant tumor the size of two footballs
from a female patient's liver.
</P>
<P>
The huge tumor weighed 12.5 kilograms, making the 41-year-old
patient appear to be pregnant, hospital staff said.
</P>
<P>
The six-hour operation was done at the Tianjin No. 3 Central
Hospital in north China.
</P>
<P>
Doctors said the patient was diagnosed with a rectal tumor 15
years ago. The cancer then spread to her liver.
</P>
<P>
She is in stable condition, according to hospital reports.
</P>
