<HEADLINE> Agriculture Bank Expands Credit Card Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China,
one of the country's four big State banks, has laid great stress
on its credit card business with the aim of sharpening its
competitive edge in preparation for the imminent entry of foreign
counterparts, said a bank official.
</P>
<P>
"Our credit cards will enable us to compete with other
commercial banks now that China's economy is making big strides
and its entry into the World Trade Organization is pending," today
's China Daily quoted Zhu Weiguo, director of the bank's credit
card department as saying.
</P>
<P>
"Commercial banks in China and other cards must have
comprehensive functions. This is our main goal," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
So far, most of China's commercial banks' credit cards only
offer services like withdrawal, deposit and bill paying.
</P>
<P>
The Agricultural Bank's Golden Spike Card has witnessed rapid
growth in recent years thanks to the establishment of a sound
management system and an active exploration of new functions, Zhu
added.
</P>
<P>
By the end of May this year, the Golden Spike card had been
issued to customers in 330 cities and the number of contracted
shops had reached 90,000.  
</P>
