<HEADLINE> China Involves in Int'l Offshore Oil Exploration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese petroleum exploration
corporation has succeeded in obtaining seismic data by conducting
2-Dimension seismic survey in the Gulf of Mexico in North America.
</P>
<P>
Two foreign petroleum companies have signed contracts with the
Chinese firm to buy the data with another four expressing intent.
</P>
<P>
The China Offshore Petroleum Physical Geographic Exploration
Corporation has cooperated with a U.S. company in exploring oil
reserves in the Gulf.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese firm has invested one million U.S. dollars. The
firm will cover the investment through selling its information and
data gained during the exploration. And 75 percent of the profits
in the initial period shall go to the Chinese side.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time that a Chinese corp. has been engaged
in international offshore petroleum exploration on risk. 
</P>
