<HEADLINE> Urgent: China to Publish White Paper on Narcotics Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Information Office of the
State Council is to publish today a white paper entitled "
Narcotics Control in China", on the Chinese government's position
on the issue and the achievements it has scored in the work.
</P>
<P>
The white paper, the first of its kind ever issued by the
Chinese government, is meant to mark the International Anti-Drug
Day.
</P>
<P>
The document comprises a foreword and the following seven
chapters: I. Sticking to the Position of Strict Drug Control; II.
Constantly Strengthening Drug Control Legislation; III. Cracking
Down on Drug-Related Crimes; IV. Exercising Strict Control over
the Precursor Chemicals; V. Treatment and Rehabilitation; VI.
Raising the Consciousness of the Entire People Vs Drugs;  VII.
Developing International Cooperation in Drug Control. 
</P>
