<HEADLINE> France Reach Semifinal after 2-1 Win Over Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 25 (Xinhua) -- World Cup winners France captured
the fourth and last semifinal berth of the Euro 2000 after Spain's
top striker Raul Gonzalez fired a last-minute penalty over the bar
to give France a 2-1 victory in the quarter-final match played in
Bruges of Belium.
</P>
<P>
France will meet Portugal in the semifinal scheduled in
Brussels on Wednesday for a place in the July 2 final.
</P>
<P>
Zinedine Zidane put France 1-0 ahead by curling in a 23-meter
free kick in the 33rd minute. With only 5 minutes later, Gaizka
Mendieta replied with a penalty to tied it at 1-all.
</P>
<P>
The French regained the lead a minute before the interval when
Patrick Vieira found Youri Djorkaeff with a diagonal pass and the
forward drove it between Santiago Canizares and his near post.
</P>
<P>
But the Spaniards, who scored two injury time goals to beat
Yugoslavia 4-3 in their third group game, should have forced extra
time when French 'keeper Fabien Barthez pulled down Abelardo
Fernandez and were awarded a penalty. But Raul blazed the spot
kick over the bar.
</P>
<P>
"We have nothing really to say." said Spanish coach Jose
Antonio after the match.
</P>
<P>
"We played well and tried to win the game but we couln't and
now we're on our way home." he added.
</P>
<P>
The French went into the game on the back of a 3-2 loss to the
Dutch, who crushed Yugoslavia 6-1 in another quarterfinal, while
the Spaniards had won two games in a row after an upset loss to
Norway in their opening game.
</P>
<P>
The French dropped Nicolas Anelka to the bench and started with
Christophe Dugarry in a five-man midfield with just Thierry Henry
up front. 
</P>
</TEXT>
