<HEADLINE> Xinhua Middle East News Summary at 2000GMT, Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Speaker of the Iranian Majlis (parliament) Mehdi
Karrubi has indicated the legislative body is determined to revise
all laws that are old-fashioned or hindering implementation of
reform programs.
</P>
<P>
As agreed by the president and the judiciary branches of the
government, legislation which are old-fashioned, outdated or
irrelevant must be revised or amended, Karrubi was quoted by the
Islamic Republic News Agency as saying on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Karrubi, secretary-general of the Assembly of Combatant Clergy
and a close ally of reform-minded President Mohammad Khatami, was
elected speaker of the Majlis on June 11. The sixth Majlis,
dominated by reformers, started work on May 27. (Iran-Laws
Revision)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat's speech on the
declaration of statehood can only harm the Middle East peace
process, said Israeli Foreign Minister David Levyon Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Arafat's speech showed that the Palestinian leader does not
want to reach an agreement with Israel," levy told the Israel
Radio.
</P>
<P>
