<HEADLINE> UNDP Helps Uganda Strengthen National Standard Organization for Quality Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) has worked with the Ugandan Government
to help boost the African nation's trade capacity and the
competitiveness of its products on the global markets, UNDP
officials said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The UNDP has joined hands with the government to commission
three modern laboratories in Kampala, the Ugandan capital, which
will develop calibrating and verifying standards with Uganda's
National Bureau of Standards, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
The laboratories were set up under the current UNDP-Uganda
Country Cooperation Framework at the cost of 1.4 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The new National Metrology Laboratory, the first of its kind
in Uganda, will provide measurement systems and calibration
services, while the Microbiology Testing Laboratory will play a
key role in safeguarding the health of consumers.
</P>
<P>
Likewise, the Electrical Laboratory is expected to support
local manufactures of electrical products to produce goods of
internationally acceptable standards.
</P>
<P>
The UNDP, set up in 1965, is the world's largest multilateral
source of grants for sustainable human development. It coordinates
most of the technical assistance provided by the United Nations
system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
