<HEADLINE> Argentina, Uruguay Ink Anti-Drug Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Argentina and Uruguay signed
Monday a memo of understanding to set up cooperation,
investigation and training mechanisms, to prevent and help drug
addictions.
</P>
<P>
The accord was signed by Secretary of Fight against Drug
Traffic, Lorenzo Cortese, on Argentina's behalf, and his Uruguayan
counterpart Raquel Magri, Monday in this capital.
</P>
<P>
According to this memo's text, both countries will foster joint
investigation in different areas, taking advantage of experiences
obtained in epidemiological observations or similar, tending to
define the profile, characteristics or perspectives of the
addictive phenomenon to diverse substances.
</P>
<P>
The accord also anticipated mutual assistance to obtain joint
diagnoses for prevention and help of undue usage of drugs.
</P>
<P>
Both parties committed themselves to maintain a more efficient
cooperation and will jointly agree communication procedures and
permanently consult each other to this respect.  
</P>
</TEXT>
