<HEADLINE> Mexico Seizes One Ton Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The cocaine, 1.475 kilograms, was discovered during inspection
with trained dogs of a cargo truck with tow in Tapachula, Chiapas
state, at the Guatemalan border, said PGR in a communique.
</P>
<P>
The drug was in 958 packages inside 41 metallic boxes hidden in
a special area in the cargo's compartment.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine discovery was carried out during an inspection of
diverse cargo bus parking lots in Tapachula, 817 kilometers
southeast of Mexico City.
</P>
<P>
Health Secretary Jose Antonio Gonzalez said Monday in Mexico's
capital that cocaine taking in the country is on the rise, where
there are about 400,000 addicts to the drug. 
</P>
