<HEADLINE> Mexico's Exports Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO, June 26 (Xinhua)-- Mexico's exports went up to 65.044
billion dollars during year 2000's first five months, increasing
by 26.2 percent compared with 1999's same period.
</P>
<P>
During year 2000's first five months, imports came to 67.155
billion dollars, 25.7 percent above 1999's same period, according
to Treasury and Public Credit Secretary.  
