<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks End Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stock ended higher
Monday as investors enthused over Philip Morris' merger
announcement ahead of the Federal Reserve's meeting on interest
rates.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 138.24 at 10,542.99
and the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 66.78 at 3,
912.12.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor'
s 500 index rose 13.83 at 1,455.31.
</P>
<P>
Stocks rallied today after Philip Morris, a cigarette and food
maker, announced on Sunday that the company planned to acquire
Nabisco holdings Corp., a snack food company, for 14.9 billion U.S.
dollars. Nabisco makes Ritz crackers, Snackwell's snacks and Oreo
cookies.
</P>
<P>
The announcement buoyed the Dow index and led broader market
higher. J.P. Morgan and Citigroup on the financial sector rose
while IBM, Hewlett-Packard and Amazon.com on the technology sector
were also higher.
</P>
<P>
But investors remained concerned about the Federal Reserve's
meeting on the monetary policy. Analysts mostly expected the
Federal Reserve to leave rates unchanged on the 27-28 meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Reserve has raised rates six times since last June
in an effort to cool off the U.S. economy and keep inflation under
control. More data have recently showed signs of the slowdown in
the economy.
</P>
<P>
But a few analysts anticipated one more quarter-percentage
point increase before ending the long cycle of current rate
increases.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 3.98 at 643.94 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 1.42 at 934.83. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 5.95 at 516.36.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-4 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,506 up, 1,362 down and 503
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 883.43 million shares from 844.74
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
